%U A395224 273765333712851131052871427,2122567668414730590074148073,94110177562207459848639528916696699,3502641042767074780517702812036495111244,4619420042407553551523306894050519062329302
%N A395224 Numerator of (zeta(4*n) / zeta(2*n)^2) * (4^n + 1) / (4^n - 1) for n >= 1.
%C A395224 This sequence can be viewed as a variation of A114362/A114363, corresponding to the Euler product over odd primes p >= 3, i.e., Product_{p>=3} (p^(2n)-1)/(p^(2n)+1).
%F A395224 a(n) = numerator( ((2 * abs(bernoulli(4*n)) * ((2*n)!)^2) / (bernoulli(2*n)^2 * (4*n)!)) * (4^n + 1) / (4^n - 1) ).
%F A395224 a(n) = numerator( (zeta(4*n)/zeta(2*n)^2) * (2^(4*n) + 2^(2*n)) / (2^(4*n) - 2^(2*n)) ).
%F A395224 a(n) = numerator( Product_{p prime > 2} (p^(2*n) - 1) / (p^(2*n) + 1) ).
%e A395224 For n = 2: (zeta(8)/zeta(4)^2) * (4^2 + 1)/(4^2 - 1) = ((Pi^8/9450) / (Pi^4/90)^2) * (17/15) = (6/7) * (17/15) = 34/35. The numerator is 34.
%e A395224 For n = 3: (zeta(12)/zeta(6)^2) * (4^3 + 1)/(4^3 - 1) = ((691*Pi^12/638512875) / (Pi^6/945)^2) * (65/63) = (691/715) * (65/63) = 691/693. The numerator is 691.
%o A395224 (PARI) {a(n) = numerator((2*abs(bernfrac(4*n))*(2*n)!^2) / (bernfrac(2*n)^2*(4*n)!) * (4^n+1)/(4^n-1))}
%Y A395224 Cf. A395225 (denominators), A000367, A002445 (Bernoulli numbers), A046988, A002432, A114362, A114363.
%K A395224 nonn,frac,new
%O A395224 1,1
